27/07/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD) will hold primary elections on 5 September to select its candidates for the upcoming general elections, according to Dan Nica of the PSD Co-ordination Bureau. Speaking Monday (26 July), he said all party members would be invited to participate in the vote, and would be able to express their opinion of each registered candidate listed. Meanwhile, the main opposition coalition PNL-PD agreed to come up with common candidate lists for the Lower House and Senate elections this fall. (Mediafax - 26/07/04)
